The paper proposes a method for training mixtures of generative models, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of deep learning. The use of discriminators and the focus on disentangling independent generative mechanisms suggests a connection to adversarial training and unsupervised learning, which are often studied in the sub-categories of cs.LG and cs.AI. The mention of generating samples also suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), where generative models are commonly used for tasks such as image and text generation. Finally, the use of deep neural networks and the focus on training procedures suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
